The national leader of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Bola Ahmed Tinubu, has urged Oyo State party members to end their crisis and make peace. The APC 2023 Presidential aspirant disclosed this while speaking to party members and delegates in Ibadan, expressing that the state party is already divided into two. Tinubu said, “Go and settle with the other members. I want you to settle with them, you will walk, you will beg. The house is divided into two. -Advertisement- “Let us end the crisis. I will still come to Ibadan later. If you don’t settle, you will lose. “I want you to vote for me and the sons of my friends and Folarin. I come here to market myself and these people. “Folarin will go and prostrate for the elders, he will beg. He will walk and go to houses to beg them. He will walk and succeed.” “You cannot win with a divided house”.